Title: Lead Software Engineer
Job_Description:
AT NORTHWESTERN MUTUAL, WE ARE STRONG, INNOVATIVE AND GROWING. WE INVEST IN OUR PEOPLE. WE CARE AND MAKE A POSITIVE DIFFERENCE.
What's the role?
We are looking for a lead software engineer to join our team. You will be responsible for leading the technical solutioning for the development and management of software services and applications that deliver the learning and recruiting experience for our financial representatives. This includes driving best practices, design patterns, strategic and tactical decisions aligning with target state architecture. You will be asked to coach fellow engineers, collaborate with several agile software engineering teams, understand the business ask and, in collaboration with Product Manager, translate that into backlog stories for multiple teams. Your teams will look to you for technical leadership and best practices to guide their work handling back-end integrations to third-party vendors, internal data stores, and the implementation of internal logic such as business rules and data access controls. Deployment environments include both internal environments and AWS cloud. As a member of the Field Learning and Talent software engineering team, you’ll have the opportunity to work on highly visible and important features that provide the digital learning and recruiting environment for our Financial Representatives.

Title: Lead Software Engineer
Job_Description:
AT NORTHWESTERN MUTUAL, WE ARE STRONG, INNOVATIVE AND GROWING. WE INVEST IN OUR PEOPLE. WE CARE AND MAKE A POSITIVE DIFFERENCE.
What's the Role?
Within the FinTech space, our Blazewater Algorithm team works at the intersection of technology and financial modeling. In 2018, our small team of capable engineers sought to re-architect our core financial-planning algorithm from the ground up, utilizing functional programming in Scala to radically rethink how heuristics-based financial modeling can be implemented at scale. In 2020, we turned our attention to stochastic modeling of portfolio risk in a concurrent, highly-distributed cloud environment. In 2021, we expanded our vision to encompass increasingly sophisticated financial instruments, with a focus on precision, accuracy, and deep levels of plan customization and mathematical optimization. Currently, we are working to take that vision of developing the next generation of financial planning applications forward, along with an increased focus on making our current suite of applications more performant and feature rich. We are looking for driven, financially-minded backend engineers with a passion for building a new class of planning software. We want to address the needs of an untapped market in personal finance!

Northwestern Mutual Life Insurance Company - Milwaukee, WI
JOB TITLE: SENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER
Job Description: The Senior Software Engineer at Northwestern Mutual Life Insurance Company in Milwaukee, Wisconsin will design, build, test and deploy FIMS APIs for NM technology organization. Participate in architecture, implementation and ensuring health of API services. Support foundational data flows for organization-wide decision making. Build out new technologies using modern architecture in the cloud. Build micro services, GraphQL and Rest APIs using Java, Spring Boot, Hibernate, Spring Data JPA, DB2 and MySQL. Build test automation using Junit, Mockito, REST-assured, Kevlar. Conduct Continuous Inspection of code quality using automatic review tools such as SonarQube. Implement Continuous Integration for the software using GitLab, GitLab CI. Deploy and support Consolidate Field Web Service applications on IBM Websphere Application Server. Deploy applications with Docker and Kubernetes on AWS Cloud. Build web application using Test-Driven development (TDD) software development process. Establish high level design, coding, manual and automated unit testing in order to adhere to acceptance criteria. Perform peer review of design, code. Coordinate with architects and infrastructure administrators for getting the environments laid out for the new platform getting built on AWS cloud. Perform version controlling code. Translate business and technical requirements into business solutions. Explain technical solutions and issues to engineering and non-technical teams. Develop server-side applications with Java/J2EE or Node.js, including develop with Spring and Spring boot developing REST API endpoints.
